WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.360
I'm tasked with updating everybody on acalabrutinib in terms of the data this year at ASH. Actually,

00:00:05.360 --> 00:00:10.080
there were a couple of practice-changing, at least to me, practice-changing abstracts,

00:00:10.080 --> 00:00:14.240
so I'll highlight some of them. First, just to put it in perspective, this is old data. Actually, I

00:00:15.760 --> 00:00:22.320
reviewed this last year here at this conference, the ElevateTN dataset, the three-arm study

00:00:22.320 --> 00:00:28.240
establishing superiority of acalabrutinib venetoclax with or without orbinutuzumab

00:00:28.240 --> 00:00:32.560
in terms of improvement in progression-free survival in comparison to

00:00:33.360 --> 00:00:41.120
investigative choice in treatment-naive patients. This is a very effective strategy. A lot of

00:00:41.120 --> 00:00:45.520
I like using it, and in fact, I'll just highlight also something important that,

00:00:45.520 --> 00:00:50.240
even though it was not part of the primary analysis for this study, there's a trend toward

00:00:50.240 --> 00:00:56.960
overall survival benefit in favor of the triple combination, which is important, obviously, in

00:00:56.960 --> 00:01:01.280
terms of the value for our patients, but also it highlights that it matters what you do in front

00:01:01.280 --> 00:01:06.240
line. A lot of us in chronic disease, a disease like this where patients are relapsing and

00:01:06.240 --> 00:01:11.200
remitting and require other lines of therapy, we usually think that perhaps they can be salvaged

00:01:11.920 --> 00:01:16.240
in subsequent lines of therapy, but in fact, here, at least the trend toward overall survival

00:01:16.240 --> 00:01:22.000
benefit suggests that, again, it matters what you do in front line and long term. Now, this

00:01:22.000 --> 00:01:25.840
strategy is very effective, but unfortunately, as you can see on the right-hand side, it comes with

00:01:25.840 --> 00:01:31.120
significant toxicity in terms of infection complications, nearly doubling the infection

00:01:31.120 --> 00:01:37.680
complications of the triplet in comparison to the doublet, and also cytopenia. So, this year at ASH,

00:01:37.680 --> 00:01:43.520
the MD Anderson folks actually presented data, and this was interesting to me and important,

00:01:43.520 --> 00:01:49.280
I think. So, this is evaluating, it's a randomized phase two study of acalabrine plus venetoclax, but

00:01:49.840 --> 00:01:54.720
the question was really early versus late institution of obinutuzumab therapy. The treatment

00:01:54.720 --> 00:02:01.040
schema is on the right-hand side, so everybody was randomized to receive either obinutuzumab early

00:02:01.040 --> 00:02:06.560
in the course, as the L of ATN, or later in the course. For those patients that received

00:02:08.400 --> 00:02:13.040
or were randomized to the obinutuzumab, they first got obinutuzumab for the first month,

00:02:13.040 --> 00:02:18.240
then they went on to receive acalabrutinib in the second month and beyond,

00:02:18.240 --> 00:02:23.600
and in the third month, venetoclax was introduced with the usual ramp-up and tumor lysis management.

00:02:23.600 --> 00:02:31.200
For those that did not get randomized to the early obinutuzumab arm, they started with two months

00:02:31.200 --> 00:02:37.120
of acalabrutinib and then went on to receive venetoclax. And at 14 months post-initiation of

00:02:37.120 --> 00:02:43.520
this regimen, there was a question of MRD assessment and response assessment, and those

00:02:43.520 --> 00:02:51.120
patients that met criteria were on the late obinutuzumab arm, or those patients that required

00:02:51.120 --> 00:02:57.360
any treatment based on MRD assessment had the option of proceeding with later course of

00:02:57.360 --> 00:03:04.880
obinutuzumab at that juncture. The primary endpoint here was really evaluating bone marrow MRD

00:03:04.880 --> 00:03:10.080
improvement. This is the study population. It's a fairly standard population. By the way,

00:03:10.080 --> 00:03:15.280
this study was restricted to high-risk patients with IGVH mutation, P53 mutation,

00:03:15.280 --> 00:03:20.960
that kind of a thing. And what I'll highlight here on the left-hand side in the panel, you can see,

00:03:21.120 --> 00:03:28.240
at the end of either the doublet or treatment therapy, this is the end of cycle 14,

00:03:28.240 --> 00:03:35.600
you can see bone marrow undetectable MRD. In the doublet, or the no, or sorry, the late

00:03:35.600 --> 00:03:44.080
obinutuzumab arm, the MRD is 26% versus the triplet is 71%. In the entire population,

00:03:44.720 --> 00:03:50.480
as you can see on the very, very bottom there on the left-hand side, 78% of the patients that

00:03:50.480 --> 00:03:58.480
were on the late obin arm went on to receive obinutuzumab in the late fashion. And by the time

00:03:58.480 --> 00:04:06.720
you get to the end of cycle 26, again in the top panel there, actually both arms have equivalent

00:04:06.720 --> 00:04:13.120
undetectable MRD. So with late institution of obinutuzumab, you actually can get the same degree

00:04:13.120 --> 00:04:19.680
of undetectable MRD. And you can, looking at CR rates by radiographic and clinical criteria,

00:04:19.840 --> 00:04:28.080
essentially equivalent whether you do early or late obinutuzumab. On the right-hand side is the

00:04:28.080 --> 00:04:33.840
undetectable MRD for high-risk disease, namely unmutated IgVH, and it mirrors the same data.

00:04:33.840 --> 00:04:39.920
At the end of cycle 14, they're substantially higher in the early obinutuzumab arm, 75% versus

00:04:39.920 --> 00:04:47.120
26%. But when you go down to the end of cycle 26, by which point both groups have received

00:04:49.200 --> 00:04:55.440
obinutuzumab, you can see equal rates of undetectable MRD. And in fact, this is also

00:04:55.440 --> 00:05:00.720
reflected here. 78% of the patients at the end of cycle 14 in the doublet arm

00:05:00.720 --> 00:05:06.960
actually were still MRD-positive, and those 51% were MRD-positive in the bone marrow,

00:05:06.960 --> 00:05:13.680
went on to receive obinutuzumab. 15 out of 17 were undetectable MRD. And for the sake of time,

00:05:13.680 --> 00:05:18.080
I'll just highlight that really the pattern continues in other categories here.

00:05:18.560 --> 00:05:26.320
Now, in terms of the toxicity, and that's what's valuable here, there's actually a trend that in

00:05:26.320 --> 00:05:33.520
the triplet or early obinutuzumab arm, there are higher deaths. This is related to COVID. This was

00:05:33.520 --> 00:05:41.120
done in the context of COVID pandemic, and so there were more deaths in the Acala/obinutuzumab Venn arm

00:05:41.120 --> 00:05:47.920
here. And in fact, looking at the toxicity, indeed, we do see significantly more toxicity here in the

00:05:47.920 --> 00:05:56.560
early obinutuzumab versus late obinutuzumab arm as manifest as infection complications. In terms of

00:05:56.560 --> 00:06:03.440
grade three complications, 26% versus 5% here, and also same thing for thrombocytopenias.

00:06:03.440 --> 00:06:10.960
And in terms of the later phase, really, once you institute the obinutuzumab even in the later phase,

00:06:10.960 --> 00:06:17.280
actually, you don't see a substantial increase in infection complications. And this is also mirroring

00:06:17.280 --> 00:06:23.120
and I'm running out of time here, but again, highlighting exactly the same thing that I've

00:06:23.120 --> 00:06:30.880
already alluded to in regards to the lower infection complications in a late obinutuzumab

00:06:30.880 --> 00:06:36.320
arm. So that to me is practice changing in the sense that if you're using this strategy, I think

00:06:36.320 --> 00:06:41.520
probably the best is to consider late institution of obinutuzumab.

00:06:42.640 --> 00:06:46.640
Now, in the limited time that I have, I'll highlight one other study. This is mirroring the

00:06:46.640 --> 00:06:56.560
FLARE study. This is a planned study for patients with older that have previously untreated CLL,

00:06:56.560 --> 00:07:02.400
but have high SEER scores or impaired renal clearance. There was a planned discontinuation

00:07:02.400 --> 00:07:08.160
of acalabrutinib monotherapy after 18 months of therapy. And for those patients that later

00:07:08.160 --> 00:07:16.000
progressed, they could reinstitute therapy with acalabrutinib again. And here, not surprisingly,

00:07:16.000 --> 00:07:20.960
the patients that discontinue actually fairly quickly continue to progress. So highlighting

00:07:20.960 --> 00:07:27.200
what has already been seen that in single agent BTK inhibitors, I think the planned discontinuation

00:07:27.200 --> 00:07:35.520
is not a good strategy. However, if you look at the IGVH mutated group, actually here, I don't

00:07:35.520 --> 00:07:40.000
know where they got the 18 months of therapy, but it actually looks like at least in that category

00:07:40.000 --> 00:07:44.880
of patients, you can potentially consider, and remember, this is older patient populations, a lot

00:07:44.880 --> 00:07:49.600
of comorbidities, there is a risk of arrhythmias and other complications. So at least in that

00:07:49.600 --> 00:07:57.200
category, very cautiously, you can potentially consider in the mutated IGVH treatment interruption.

00:07:57.200 --> 00:07:58.800
So I'll stop there.
